http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Former-Sikkim-Governor-V.-Rama-Rao-passes-away/article14005153.ece

Veteran BJP leader and former Sikkim Governor V. Rama Rao died at a city hospital here on Sunday after prolonged illness. He was 81. He is survived by his wife, son and daughter-in-law.The BJP leader was suffering from severe lung infection and was hospitalised about a month ago.Rama Rao was a lawyer and practised at the Andhra Pradesh High Court. He was elected as MLC on four occasions in the erstwhile Andhra Pradesh State Legislature. While he served for three full terms in 1966, 1972 and 1978, the Legislative Council was abolished during his fourth term after his election from Graduates Constituency in 1984. He was also imprisoned during Emergency Rama Rao, who joined the Jan Sangh in 1956, was BJP national vice-president.He was the president of BJP unit in united Andhra Pradesh twice from 1992-96. He served as Sikkim Governor from October 25, 2002, to October 25, 2007.